revision.text:
This page is an archive of the discussion about the proposed deletion of the article below. '''This page is no longer live.''' Further comments should be made on the article's talk page rather than here so that this page is preserved as an historic record.
The result of the debate was '''DELETE'''. [[User:Golbez|Golbez]] 18:34, May 17, 2005 (UTC) ===[[The New Naptilians]]=== This is a comic book written in his spare time by a schoolboy; it has no encyclopædic content. [[User:Mel Etitis|Mel Etitis]] ([[User talk:Mel Etitis|Μελ Ετητης)]] 10:15, 9 May 2005 (UTC) *'''Delete''' Do you reckon it's worth running a VFD on [[Geppers Creepers]] too? [[User:The JPS|The JPS]] 11:22, 9 May 2005 (UTC) **I did think of that; I'm something of a [[m:Mergism|mergist]]/[[m:Inclusionism|inclusionist]], though, so I'm inclined to give articles the benefit of the doubt if I can. I couldn't bring myself to vote to keep it, though. [[User:Mel Etitis|Mel Etitis]] ([[User talk:Mel Etitis|Μελ Ετητης)]] 11:54, 9 May 2005 (UTC) ***'''Note:''' [[Geppers Creepers]] is now listed on VFD. [[User:The JPS|The JPS]] 23:15, 9 May 2005 (UTC) *'''Delete''' Nowhere near notable enough. [[User:Starblind|Andrew Lenahan - Starblind]] 13:41, May 9, 2005 (UTC) *'''Delete'''. There seems to be a complete lack of influence or popularity to this one. [[User:Average Earthman|Average Earthman]] 19:16, 9 May 2005 (UTC) *'''Delete''', not notable. [[User:Megan1967|Megan1967]] 01:54, 10 May 2005 (UTC) :''This page is now preserved as an archive of the debate and, like some other VfD subpages, is no longer 'live'. Subsequent comments on the issue, the deletion, or the decision-making process should be placed on the relevant 'live' pages. '''Please do not edit this page'''.''
